initial statement:
 952
Your Honor,

I stand before the court today as a 55-year-old individual with no prior criminal record. It is with great humility that I plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified.

I must acknowledge the gravity of my actions and express my deep regret for my lapse in judgment. Two months ago, I was disqualified from driving due to a series of speeding incidents. Despite this court's order, I made the ill-advised decision to get behind the wheel and drive to a supermarket. In hindsight, I realize the importance of adhering to the consequences imposed upon me by the court.

I wish to assure the court that my actions were not driven by any malicious intent or disregard for the law. Rather, I simply failed to consider the implications of my decision in the heat of the moment. I am truly embarrassed by my failure to abide by the court's previous order.

Recognizing the severity of my offense, I am fully committed to taking the necessary steps to rectify my actions and prevent any recurrence in the future. I am willing to participate in any appropriate courses or programs that the court deems necessary for my rehabilitation. Additionally, I am open to making any amends or compensating for the harm caused by my disregard for the law. 

I understand that pleading guilty is in itself a mitigating factor, and I accept full responsibility for my actions. 

I respectfully request the court's leniency and consideration of my earnest efforts to improve myself and make amends. I assure the court that I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience and I am committed to becoming a law-abiding citizen.

Thank you for your attention.

Sincerely,
David Lambert
